sentence.text: We have identified nine genes of interest that appear to be involved in cervical cancer development: SPARCL1, synaptonemal complex assembly, mitotic cytokinesis, PRC1, TOP2A, LAMP3, KIF20A, cellular response to DNA damage stimulus, and APOBEC3B.

entity.text: cellular response to DNA damage stimulus

sentence.text: Further, we analyzed the expression of these nine genes during the progression of cervical cancer, and found that post-translational protein modification is also related to precancerous lesions and migration processes during cervical cancer pathogenesis.
